com.thinkaurelius.titan.core

Interface VertexLabel

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Element, Idfiable, Namifiable, Removable, TitanElement, TitanSchemaElement, TitanSchemaType, TitanVertex, com.tinkerpop.blueprints.Vertex
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    InternalVertexLabel
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseVertexLabel, VertexLabelVertex

    public interface VertexLabel
extends TitanVertex, TitanSchemaType
    A vertex label is a label attached to vertices in a Titan graph. This can be used to define the nature of a vertex.

    Internally, a vertex label is also used to specify certain characteristics of vertices that have a given label.

    Author:
    Matthias Broecheler (me@matthiasb.com)
